28 hours of sunshine</b> per month, or 7.6 hours of sunshine per day. This is <b class="red">3.39% less</b> than the average for Italy and <b class="red">4.64% less</b> than the average for the region of Toscana.<br><br> Throughout the year, <b>it rains on average 7.38 days per month</b>, which is <b>an ordinary amount of precipitation</b> for an Italian province.<br><br>Throughout the autumn and winter season, there are usually <b class="green">4.55 days per month with fog</b> and <b>1.52 cold days per month</b> with perceived temperatures below 3°C.  In the summer, there are on average <b>20.8 hot days per month</b> with perceived temperatures above 30°C.<br><span class="separator"></span><br><center><h3>Weather Now</h3><a class="weatherwidget-io" href="https://forecast7.com/en/43d9310d91/pistoia/" data-label_1="Pistoia" data-label_2="Toscana" data-font="Roboto" data-icons="Climacons Animated" data-mode="Forecast" data-theme="clear" data-basecolor="rgba(155, 205, 245, 0.59)" data-textcolor="#000441">name Region.Name</a><script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src='https://weatherwidget.io/js/widget.min.js';fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,'script','weatherwidget-io-js');</script></center></span><h2>Cost of Living</h2><span id="CoL">The <b>average monthly income in Pistoia is around 1619.58€</b>, which is close to the average for Italy.<br><br>The estimated cost of living is around 1597.44€ per month for an individual or 2402.91€ per month for a family of 4. The cost for renting a small apartment (2-3 bedrooms) in a main city area is around 1173.34€ per month.<br><br>Overall, <b class="green">Pistoia is affordable</b> compared to other Italian provinces. Living in Pistoia is around <b class="green">3.19% cheaper than the average</b> of all Italian provinces.</span><h2>Quality of Life</h2><h3>Healthcare</h3><span id="healthcare"><b>Healthcare in Pistoia is <b class="green">above average</b></b>. For every 10k inhabitants, there are around undefined pharmacies, 9.08 general practitioners and 22.9 specialized doctors per 10k inhabitants. <b>Average life expectancy in Pistoia is  very high at 83.4 years of age.</b><br><span class="separator"></span><br></span><h3>Education</h3><span id="education">Pistoia has a <b class="red">lower-than-average percentage of high school graduates</b>, around 58.7%; and a <b class="red">lower-than-average percentage of university graduates</b>, around 24.9%. The average number of completed <b>years of schooling</b> for people over 25 is 10.2, which is not far from the national average of 10.44.  There are <b>no universities</b> in this province.<br><span class="separator"></span><br></span><h3>Leisure</h3><span id="leisure">Pistoia has <b>somewhat decent nightlife</b> with 2.8 bars and 4.05 restaurants per 10k inhabitants. <br><span class="separator"></span><br></span><h3>Crime and Safety</h3><span id="crimeandsafety">The province of Pistoia is overall <b class="green">moderately safe for expats</b>. As of 2021, there are an average of <b>3056.7 reported crimes per 100k inhabitants</b>. This is <b class="red">7.79% higher than the national average</b>.<br><br>There have been around <b>0.4 deadly road accidents</b> and <b>11.5 serious work-related injuries</b> per 10k people in Pistoia. This is respectively <b class="green">25.93% less driving accidents than average</b> and <b class="green">10.85% less work accidents than average</b>.<br><br>Car theft is reportedly <b class="green">69.03% lower than average</b> with only 21.84 cases per 100k inhabitants. Reports of house thefts are <b class="red">85.41% higher than average</b> with 324.51 cases per 100k inhabitants. Cases of robbery are not totally uncommon, around <b class="red">30.98% higher than average</b> with 29 reports per 100k inhabitants. <br><span class="separator"></span><br></span><h3>Transport</h3><span id="transport"><b>Public transport in Pistoia</b> is <b class="red">lacking</b>, and <b class="green">traffic is below average</b>. There are on average 0.65 active vehicles per person, against a national average of 0.66. <br><br>Around 0.74km per 10k inhabitants of the main city in Pistoia consist of bicycle lanes. This makes Pistoia <b class="green">somewhat bike-friendly by Italian standards</b>. <br><span class="separator"></span><br></span><h2>Discover</h2><span id="promo"><center><h3>Recommended Tours in Toscana</h3></center><div data-vi-partner-id="P00045447" data-vi-language="en" data-vi-currency="USD" data-vi-partner-type="AFFILIATE" data-vi-url="https://www.viator.com/Tuscany/d206-ttd" data-vi-total-products="6" data-vi-campaign="Pistoia"></div><script async="" src="https://www.viator.com/orion/partner/widget.js"></script><br><span class="separator"></span><br></span></div></body></html>